job_description:
• Work under supervision of professors (research areas: data science, artificial intelligence, applied mathematics), economists, and senior software developers;
• Contribute to the development of our flagship product (i.e., the intelligent platform for finan cial information retrieval and analysis) through designing and improving search algorithms that are based on a CityU patent;
• Design and implement parallel computing solutions for large -scale machine learning algorithms;
• Evaluate and select appropriate cloud computing services to support large -scale machine learning projects;
• Use economic theory to guide model design, perform statistical hypothesis testing, and create inferences and recommendations based on economic, statistical, and data science model s;
• Assist in developing interactive dashboards for financial markets and macroeconomy;
• Build and maintain databases (PostgreSQL); collect structured and unstructured data using various techniques, e.g., web crawling;
• Write research level publications  or technical white papers with a clear explanation of complicated technical concepts to audiences with diverse business/scientific backgrounds;
• Communicate with team members and present at internal and external events such as weekly company meetings, re search conferences/seminars.

Job Requirements :
• Undergraduate/masters/PhD candidates in Data Science, Statistics, Economics, Engineering, or any related STEM fields from Hong Kong universities (final -year students are welcomed as long as you remain a stude nt during your internship);
• Familarity with natural language processing algorithms (e.g., topic model, TF -IDF, sentiment analysis);
• Experience with the implementation of machine learning algorithms (e.g., logistic regression, SVM, neural network);
• Experience with cloud computing platforms such as AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure;
• Familiarity with distributed computing frameworks such as Spark, Hadoop, and MPI;
• Strong coding skills with Python, R, and/or Stata;
• Fluency in English and Chinese (Mandar in or Cantonese) and demonstrated exceptional ability to write structured and clear reports/papers in at least one of 
the two languages;

Preferred Qualifications :
• Good understanding of macroeconomics, development economics, and ESG;
• Proficiency in the use of databases such as Wind, Bloomberg, Capital IQ, etc.;
• Knowledge of a professional BI tool such as Power BI, Tableau, Qlikview, etc.;
• Exceptional leadership and management skills.
